    • Method Detail

      • setConfig

        void setConfig(JSAPResult config)
        throws DataProviderException
        Set the config for this data provider. This method should check if all required arguments are set using com.martiansoftware.jsap.JSAPResult#contains(String) and throw an DataProviderException if any arguments are missing or invalid. If no exception is thrown it is assumed that everything is ok.
        Parameters:
        config - config result that was created using the main arguments
        Throws:
        DataProviderException - if arguments in the config are missing or invalid
